        <num>46-3-324</num>
        <content>
          <p>After the corporate existence has begun, an organization meeting of the board of directors named in the articles of incorporation shall be held, either within or outside of this state, at the call of any incorporator, for the purpose of adopting bylaws, electing officers, and transacting such other business as properly may come before the meeting. The incorporator or incorporators calling the meeting shall give at least three days' notice thereof by mail to each director so named, which notice shall state the time and place of the meeting.</p>
          <p>(Code 1933, ยง 34C-705, enacted by Ga. L. 1981, p. 1587, ยง 1.)</p>
